#X text 20 17 The [asr~] object is an attack/sustain/release envelope. By only setting the release phase \, we can also implement just a 'decay' envelope. Note that in order for this to work you need to trigger it with an impulse \, which immediately goes to the release phase., f 72;
#X text 358 478 The object has more features and also has a 'lag' mode \, which is in fact a one-pole filter like [decay~]. We'll see more about this object later on. You can go ahead and check its help file right now anyway., f 21;
#X text 67 342 Note that [envgen~] \, with all its several features and curve settings \, also includes the same curve factor used in [asr~] \, also used in [smooth~]. Just set the curve value as a float. You can see above it also has a status right outlet \, which shows when the envelope is done., f 61;
